Is it is possible for lock to linger for some reason even though the NN process was killed? If so, can we add descriptive error message that describes how an admin can get around it after ensuring no namenode process is running?

Isn't the patch as simple as:
{noformat}
      try {
        res = file.getChannel().tryLock();
+       lockF.deleteOnExit();
      } catch(OverlappingFileLockException oe) {
        ...
      } catch(IOException e) {
        ...
      }
{noformat}
